<section id="content" role="main" class="group support-page">
  <header class="page-header group">
    <div class="full-width">
      <h1>Linking to GOV.UK from other websites</h1>
    </div>
  </header>


  <div class="support-container full-width group">
    <article role="article" class="group">
      <div class="inner">

        <div class="top-issues">
          <h2>On this page:</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="#text-links">Can I link to GOV.UK?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#logos">Can I use the logo to link to GOV.UK?</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2 id="text-links">Can I link to GOV.UK?</h2>
        <p>Of course! But instead of linking to the home page, consider linking directly to <a href="https://www.gov.uk">GOV.UK</a> pages that are useful to the people visiting your site. The best link text to use is often the title of the page you're linking to.</p>

        <p>If you want to create a link to the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/">GOV.UK</a> home page, please use <a href="https://www.gov.uk/">GOV.UK</a> (in capitals) as the link text.</p>

        <h2 id="logos">Can I use the logo to link to GOV.UK?</h2>
        <p>We would prefer it if you used text to link to a relevant page within <a href="https://www.gov.uk/">GOV.UK</a></p>


      </div>
    </article>

  </div>
</section>

